org.orgName: District Court of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory

body.p: Territory of Washington } ss. County of King
In the matter of the application for a Writ of Habeas Corpus of Gustave Gunderson.

The above matter coming on this 27th day of June 1887. and before me R.A. Jones Chief Justice of the Supreme Court of said Territory Chief Justice of the Supreme Court of Washington Territory: and its Sheriff of King County, to whom said writ was directed having made return there of as required by law: and J.T Ronalo, the District attorney appearing on behalf of the territory and Burke + Haller appearing on behalf of the applicant, and it appearing to my satisfaction that there is no legal cause shown for the restraint of said Gustave Gunderson, or for the continuation of such restraint, it is now ordered that said Gustave Gunderson be and he is hereby discharged from custody.
In the matter of the application for a writ of Habeas Corpus
James Seavey, Clerk. By W.E. Ledgerwood, Deputy Clerk.
